        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "Brooks Pointer in Object class",
        "body": "<p>In Android SDK 21 in <code>Object.java<\/code> code, i came across the term &quot;Brooks Pointer&quot;. I read the post <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20151018210228/https://rkennke.wordpress.com/2013/10/23/shenandoah-gc-brooks-pointers/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">&quot;Shenandoah GC: Brooks pointers&quot;<\/a> but i am not getting a clear picture of it. In the post, it is described as a reference to the Object itself in the heap. But what is the use of it?<br />\nHow will it help in Garbage collection and Object evacuation?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 30379391,
